  FAMOUS PEOPLE
============================================================

Name:          Confucius
Lived:         551 - -479
Nationality:   Chinese
Field:         Philosophy
Known For:     Confucianism
Contribution:  Ren, li, filial piety; still shapes East Asian society 2,500 years later
Quote:         "It does not matter how slowly you go as long as you do not stop."

Name:          Stephen Hawking
Lived:         1942 - 2018
Nationality:   English
Field:         Physics
Known For:     Black hole radiation
Contribution:  Proved black holes emit radiation; A Brief History of Time; communicated science publicly
Quote:         "Intelligence is the ability to adapt to change."

Name:          Charles Darwin
Lived:         1809 - 1882
Nationality:   English
Field:         Biology
Known For:     Evolution by Natural Selection
Contribution:  On the Origin of Species; explained diversity of life on Earth
Quote:         "It is not the strongest that survives, but the most adaptable."

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Comparative Advantage
Category:   International Trade
Definition: Countries gain by specializing in what they produce most efficiently
Formula:    Compare opportunity cost ratios
Economist:  David Ricardo
Example:    China makes electronics cheaply; USA makes pharma cheaply; both gain trading

Concept:    Gini Coefficient
Category:   Statistics
Definition: Measures income inequality from 0 (equal) to 1 (one person has all)
Formula:    G = 1 - 2∫L(x)dx
Economist:  Corrado Gini
Example:    USA Gini ~0.41; Denmark ~0.29; South Africa ~0.63

Concept:    GDP
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Total value of all goods and services produced in a country annually
Formula:    GDP = C + I + G + (X-M)
Economist:  Simon Kuznets
Example:    USA GDP 2023: $27.4 trillion; China: $17.9 trillion

